<br>
Some places pets are OK, in others, no.  At the SS, its fine, in Inny's chamber, its fine.  Even at the Maestro its ok if you stay near the Throne.  So a good mage must learn where its not ok, and there are alot of places (mainly on the 2nd floor)<br>
<br>
Chardok is the same way, some places are ok, some are not.  But a mage's fire pet is GODLY against the queen and king.  Their almost immunity to fire makes them a crucial asset.<br>
<br>
This problem will never end until Verant fixes all the pathing issues, so the mages that are less-then-par at pet control dont get people killed.  But we can all guess when that is going to happen.<br>
<br>
Last thing I want to say, is in my experience, when a raid goes south, and people die, the first person to get blamed is the damn mage or necro pet.  I have been on raids where 6 mobs were pulled in, I never told my pet to attack, in fact I made sure the pet was following me around and not in combat.  Still, after all the rez, some people were saying &quot;that damn pet started that train&quot; NONE OF THE MOBS EVER TOUCHED THE PET!!!<br>
<br>
In fact, the mobs ran into the group and right past us to the bard playing his songs...<br>
<br>
So even when the pet does not cause the train, if pets still get blamed, people walk away thinking it was the pet, which adds to Pet-Hate syndrome<br>
<br>
BAH!!!!<br>
<br>
the ONLY thing ALL of us can do to improve this, is practice good pet control, and know when not to have a pet.  If we all did that, we would not have this problem. <p><center><img src="http://www.homestead.com/balandar/files/eandori.jpg" width=173
